To make two clients (Angular and Messenger) communicate with each other through a Fastify server, you will need to set up a communication channel between the clients and the server. Here's a high-level overview of how you can achieve this:

1. Set up Fastify server:
First, create a Fastify server and define the necessary routes and hooks.

```javascript
const fastify = require('fastify')({ logger: true })

fastify.get('/', async (request, reply) => {
  return { message: 'Welcome to the Fastify server!' }
})

fastify.listen(3000, (err, address) => {
  if (err) throw err
  fastify.log.info(`server listening on ${address}`)
})
```
